// Comptime console output goes through the real console object and is
// emitted DURING compilation — so it precedes all runtime output, on every
// engine that runs in-process (--run / --ir share one stdout).
// @no-roundtrip: that same compile-time stdout interleaves with the --expand
// source dump, so the captured artifact is not pure source (Phase 4 §6).
comptime console.writeln("[build] table ready");
console.writeln("runtime output");
